From 63091ac644fa6cb5a2cc6ee6f08def694a6fe19c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sushant Butta <sbutta@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 20 Jun 2025 00:03:58 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 4/5] UPSTREAM: DP: wifi: ath12k: Segregation of Monitor pdev
 Objects in Unified Driver Framework

With the Unified Driver framework, to support different monitor
variants (quad ring and dual ring) model and for better view of
monitor object, segregate monitor-related rings and objects from
the PDEV DP object and defining them in the monitor pdev object.
Allocation and deallocation of the monitor object are done dynamically.

Patch-dependency:
	0402-0003-UPSTREAM-DP-wifi-ath12k-Refactor-ring-allocation-set.patch

Co-developed-by: Alok Singh <aloksing@qti.qualcomm.com>
Signed-off-by: Alok Singh <aloksing@qti.qualcomm.com>
Signed-off-by: Sushant Butta <sbutta@qti.qualcomm.com>
